article.headline: Idaho 70, San Jose St. 64
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Deremy Geiger scored 16 points and Connor Hill added 12 on four 3-pointers to lead Idaho to a 70-64 victory against San Jose State on Saturday night. Landon Tatum added 10 points, and Djim Bandoumel and Kyle Barone had nine rebounds each for the Vandals (18-12, 9-5 Western Athletic), who have won seven of their last eight games and are the No. 3 seed in next week's conference tournament in Las Vegas. Idaho faces sixth-seeded Hawaii in a first-round game on Thursday. James Kinney had 19 points and made five 3-pointers for the Spartans (9-21, 1-13), who are the No. 8 seed and play top-seeded Nevada in the first round. Keith Shamburger added 14 points and Wil Carter 12. San Jose State trailed 54-50 with 3:54 remaining, but Idaho closed out the game by scoring all its points with free throws. The Vandals made 16 of 22 from the line down the stretch.
